  "text": "Third, how stable is the selection vs. evaluation parsing during learning? Our survey focused on neural responses in well-trained animals. However, neural ensembles in the rat dorsomedial striatum and monkey dorsal striatum display striking changes during different stages of learning, particularly in cue presentation, choice and post-decision epochs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . It is interesting to speculate whether single neurons switch between contributing to selection or to evaluation during training. If we assume that neural ensembles encoding selection and evaluation are stable, how do they interact with each other? Simultaneous recordings of multiple striatal neurons on rewardbased or perceptual decision tasks could shed light on this question.",
